I"<p>When with their mother, the infant’s <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/stress-is-peak-exploitation">stress response</a> is strongly blunted because “mom is taking care.” In machine learning, models undergo several warm-up steps which blunt the magnitude of the error signal, in an effort to <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/psychological-foraging-resembles-simulated-annealing">avoid early overfitting</a>. What has been developed as an engineering solution might have been devised by evolution long ago.</p>
